@node install "Installation"
@wordwrap

@{jcenter}@{fg highlight}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{fg text}
@{jleft}
ModePro does not require any other libraries than those that come with AmigaDOS 2.1+.  However, WB2.04 users will need version 38 of the  asl.library.

To install ModePro:@{lindent 2}
Copy ModePro to the Sys:WBStartup drawer.
Copy ModeProPrefs to the Sys:Prefs drawer.
Copy the catalog files to the appropriate Sys:Locale/Catalogs/language drawer if you want.
@{lindent 0}

One of these days I'll write an installer script for it.
@endnode

@node gui "Preference's Interface"
@wordwrap

@{jcenter}@{fg highlight}@{b}Preference's Interface@{ub}@{fg text}
@{jleft}

Once ModePro is running, there are a few ways to bring up the preferences interface:@{lindent 2}
@{b}· Use the hotkey (default left-amiga p)
· Use the Commodities Exchange program, click on ModePro and select Show Interface.
· Run ModePro again.
· Run ModeProPrefs in the sys:Prefs drawer.@{ub}
@{lindent 0}

The interface should resemble this:
@{jcenter}
@{bg fill}@{fg filltext} ModePro Preferences: Hotkey = <lcommand p>                          | ]@{fg text}@{bg background}   
